This paper discusses the methodology of sampling the Internet network and inferring its topology characteristics, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses statistical inference, which is a common topic in statistics (cs.ST) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches upon the problem of determining network size, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the merging of spanning trees, which is a graph theory concept (cs.DS).
